<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She tied the knot in a stunning Las Vegas ceremony in September.</p>

<p>And Lily Allen made sure to flash her dazzling engagement and wedding rings as she enjoyed an evening at Scott’s Restaurant in Mayfair, London, on Wednesday night. </p>

<p>The Smile singer, 35, appeared to be in good spirits as she braved the drizzly rain and walked along the street in a warm black coat.</p>

<p>Dazzling: Lily Allen appeared to be in good spirits as she stepped out in London on Wednesday with her wedding and engagement rings on full display</p>

<p>Lily wrapped up warm for the evening in a tailored black jacket which came down past her knees.</p>

<p>She paired the statement piece with some beige wide-leg trousers and completed her ensemble with some white sandals.</p>

<p>The beauty wore her dark locks tied back into a high ponytail and wore a touch of makeup including a nude lipstick to accentuate her pretty features.</p>

<p>Wrapped up: The singer donned a large black jacket and beige trousers for the outing</p>

<p>The outing comes after Lily put on a showstopping display while showing off her figure for the camera and pulling her very best pose during a workout session.</p>

<p>She paired a Nike crop top with a pair of high-waisted leggings as she stood in her jam-packed wardrobe which gave a glimpse of her lavish wardrobe. </p>

<p>Lily was also indulging in some pampering as she whitened her teeth, while her new husband has remained the in States since the wedding. </p>

<p>The couple, who were first romantically linked in 2019, surprised fans by revealing they had exchanged vows in a wedding officiated by an Elvis Presley impersonator. </p>

<p>Flaunt it: Lily showed off her bling as she held up one hand to her face</p>

<p>Details: The beauty wore her dark locks tied back into a high ponytail and added a touch of makeup including a nude lipstick to accentuate her pretty features</p>

<p>Interesting: Lily completed her ensemble with a pair of white Birkenstock sandals</p>

<p>Sharing photos to his Instagram shortly after the ceremony, Harbour wrote: 'In a wedding officiated by the king himself... </p>

<p>'The people's princess wed her devoted, low born, but kind credit card holder in a beautiful ceremony lit by the ashen skies courtesy of a burning state miles away in the midst of a global pandemic.' </p>

<p>Lily opted for a short white double-breasted dress with a bateau neckline, black buttons, and a belted waist teamed with black suede platforms heels and a small bouquet of pink flowers.   </p>

<p>On the go: Lily recently completed two weeks of quarantine after returning from her Las Vegas wedding</p>

<p>Home time: Lily was seen jumping into a cab as she made a stylish departure</p>

<p>Happy: The singer could not stop smiling as she made her way towards the taxi</p>

<p>Lily went onto share a snap with David outside the wedding chapel, before revealing they celebrated their marriage but grabbing fast food from In-N-Out. </p>

<p>They were joined by Lily's children Ethel, eight, and Marnie, seven, from her first marriage to Sam Cooper as they tucked into their fast food outside. </p>

<p>According to TMZ, Lily and David registered to marry in Sin City at the end of last week, with a license valid for 12 months. </p>

<p>Details: The star's engagement ring caught the light as she made her way home on Wednesday</p>

<p>Public records obtained by the website state the expiration date for the license is September 6 2021 - meaning they were to wed within the year.</p>

<p>Lily's first wedding was very different - an idyllic ceremony in Gloucestershire in 2011 to Sam Cooper, whom she eventually split from in 2016.</p>

<p>The newlyweds divide their time between the UK and US and sparked engagement rumours in May, when Lily revealed a distinctive looking ring on social media.    </p>

<p>Warm wishes: Lily and David tied the knot in a stunning Vegas ceremony on September 7th</p>
